<br>
I got a port to Iceclad ( love those kind druids) then he showed me the way to Eastern Wastes. when you zone in you are at the top of a bridge. Nothing really here that will kill you. <br>
<br>
When i got down the bridge i followed the shore line to the right. You go past a Rygorr camp and a Coldain camp.<br>
after a while i got to a singel tree near the shore line. i saw a druid and asked if he thought the exp was good. hehe of course he answerd yes. I was reccomended to stick with Ulthork Hunters and Walrusses( Some walrusses coned green) . <br>
I soloed those for half a lvl (3 HOURS!!!) then i decided to try on the warriors  who walked by.<br>
These were wonderful exp and as i killed i saw my exp meeter go up fairly quick. in 2 hours i got the last half of my lvl and dinged the magical lvl of 42 =-) .<br>
Next day i continued my hunting and in short i dinged 43.<br>
<br>
The 43 lvl was kinda toughf. most hunters conned green. some exp green and occationaly some light blue, warriors still provided a good exp santuary in these wastelands.<br>
Though it took some time i got to the killer lvl 44=).<br>
<br>
+ with this place<br>
<br>
*There are alot of druids that are willing to supply SoW at this place ( wich is a strong +)<br>
+ your loot is Velium items, Ulthork armor( drops really common) Ulthork tusks wich sell to players for 50pp or can be exchanged to different gems in Cobolt scar,and the magical Walruss tooth ( drops from the Ulthorks as well)<br>
+ Good exp untill lvl 43 wich is kinda toughf here (about 7 hours playing)<br>
<br>
- With this place<br>
<br>
* if you aint carful with your pulls you might get adds as the green things also posses alot of agro.<br>
*If you get unlucky sometimes there might be a druid that is well known with the fact that they can pull more then 1 ulthork=)<br>
* without SoW youll need some stamina for all those get further away jumps=)<br>
<br>
I surley think that the good things over weight the bad things with quite alot. tho there are somethings to think about here<br>
<br>
* sometimes the Ulthorks can hinde at the cliff dropping down to the water, this can end up as a add. Always have Gate prepared and if you pull 2 gate back.<br>
<br>
*bind at the bridge, this will eliminate the time getting back to the camp if you get adds or die.<br>
<br>
*The warriors hit harder and have more HP then the Hunters so i would pratice my skills on hunters befour i go kill warriors.<br>
<br>
*The lvl 39 firepet owns these bad guys, though on warriors you might have to cast in a few heals on em<br>
<br>
*Supply your pet with the Velium weponds that drop here. They give him an extra DD proc=)<br>
<br>
Well this is all i can supply. Sure this hopes my friends and you have the same luck as i had here. oh btw, the total amount of money i made in these 3 lvls is 1567pp. just summon those dimention bags=) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugrumples.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grumples</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#333333>(10/2/01 6:44:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels3943.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: lvl 41 to 44 some loot</span><hr size=1> Keep those ulthork tusks.  There a quest you can do with them in Cobalt Scar.  It's worth it if you're getting XP from the ulthorks at the same time.<br>
<br>
I also usually fitted my pet with the ulthork armor.  I'm too lazy to go back and sell it to players, and it gets heavy.  Going with the theory that AC items help the pet, I handed em off.<br>
<br>
The rhinos are doable if you don't mind frenzy kiting them.  Blast em a couple times, turn pet taunting off with the pet having expedience and just run around while the pet beats on em.  Anytime they turn on the pet, blast em again.  The 39 pet won't live long if you let it tank.  It's not really worth it, but sometimes nobody is killing the rhinos, and there will be 0 ulthorks and like 2 dozen rhinos.<br>
<br>
Rhinos are easy XP if you group with a druid.  Pull rhino with Malise, druid snares, then uses their 10 mana animal fear, then your pet beats on it for free.<br>
